On Thu, 21 Oct 2004, Andy wrote:

> > hey great idea, double ground
> 
> 
> This is a great idea, but both ground cables need to be able to handle the
> full current load. If you're using one of those cables that have a large lug
> and a smaller yellow butt splice connector, don't do it. If the large lug
> were to develop a problem (say, it comes loose), the smaller wire would be
> forced to carry the full load of current. One twist of the starter under
> these circumstances would light the small wire right up.
> 
